item.title: Introduction: Choices Pet Sitters
item.description:
Your pets are part of your family, and as such they deserve the best. Many times moving them to the loud, unfriendly environment of a traditional boarding kennel can cause more harm than good especially if they are elderly or have health issues. Pets often come back with diarrhea, thinner from not eating, or just plain full of anxiety. And wait until you have to go out of town again... Good luck finding them to get them in the car next time even if they are only going to the groomer!Pets (and people) are most comfortable and thrive in the environment they've come to know as their own, with their own familiar smells, sights, visitors, and routines. No one knows this better than a pet parent who has to chase their furry friend around the house in an effort to get ready to catch a plane, train, or bus. And what boarding kennel takes snakes, hamsters, ferrets, Chinchillas, fish, pigs, horses, or birds?The alternative... Professional In-Home Pet Care and Dog Walking services. No longer will you have to spend 10 minutes rounding up your pet to corral them in a crate, another 30 to drive them to the vet, and another 30 minutes to get back to the house to grab your packed bags to head to your destination.Serving the North Georgia Area since 2005, Choices Pet Sitters is a North Georgia based Professional In-Home Pet Care / Dog Walking Service. Our personal, customized services are designed to eliminate the added stress on you and your pets. Our pet sitters follow your pet's daily routines, while keeping your pet in the comfortable environment that he or she is accustomed to being in each day. Services are customized to your pet's needs as much as possible including mid-day walks for a new puppy, elderly dog, or rambunctious teen aged dog that just needs a little attention and potty break.Call Choices Pet Sitters today at (678) 253-PETS for more information on In-Home Pet Care in Pickens and North Cherokee Counties in Georgia.
